## Where They Drop Off — REVISED

The full persona-card-based conversion funnel within a **7-day window** reveals two distinct chokepoints:

**Pricing Page → View Pricing → Persona → Plan → Subscribed**

- 15,285 → 6,649 → 6,360 → 5,660 → 412

| Step | Step Conv. | Cumulative Conv. | Avg Time |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Pricing Page → Click "View Pricing" | **43.5%** | 43.5% | ~42 sec |
| View Pricing → Select Persona | **95.7%** | 41.6% | ~9 sec |
| Select Persona → Click Plan | **89.0%** | 37.0% | ~15 sec |
| Click Plan → Subscribe | **7.3%** | **2.7%** | ~9.5 hours |
| **Overall: Pricing → Subscribed** | — | **2.7%** | — |

Within a **30-minute same-session window**, the persona-through-plan flow performs almost identically (42.6% → 95.5% → 88.5%), but plan-to-subscribe drops to 5.3% (290 conversions). This means **70% of pricing-driven subscriptions happen in the same session**, with the remaining 30% converting within 1-7 days.

**The two real leaks are now clearly identifiable:**

**Leak #1 — Top of page: 56.5% never click "View Pricing"** (~8,636 users). This aligns directly with the scroll depth data showing 39% bounce without scrolling past 5% and 56% don't reach 20% scroll depth. The persona cards may not be visible or compelling enough above the fold for a majority of visitors. These users are landing, seeing the hero area, and leaving without ever engaging with the pricing flow.

**Leak #2 — Plan screen to checkout: 92.7% of plan-clickers don't subscribe** (5,660 users saw plans, only 412 subscribed). This is the largest absolute opportunity. These users demonstrated clear purchase intent — they clicked a coverage type, chose a persona, reviewed plans with pricing — and still didn't convert. Something at or after the plan selection screen is losing them. Potential causes include price objection after seeing actual numbers, confusion about plan differences, friction in the checkout/sign-up process, or the need to create an account before purchasing.

**What's NOT broken:** The middle of the funnel. The persona card → persona selection → plan selection flow converts at 95.7% and 89.0% respectively — these steps are working extremely well. Users who engage with the first card are almost guaranteed to complete the entire pricing discovery experience. Optimization efforts should focus on the two ends, not the middle.

