Monthly plans consistently convert at **2-5x the rate** of their yearly equivalents, and convert faster (~2.5 hours vs. ~10-12 hours). The highest-volume plan (Pro Yearly at 5,464 clicks) has one of the lower conversion rates at 7.3%, while Creator Monthly — the lowest price point — converts at 35.9% despite getting the fewest clicks (323). This suggests lower upfront commitment significantly reduces the final conversion barrier, and that more prominent monthly pricing could improve overall conversion at the potential expense of initial ACV.

A few standout patterns:

**Creator Monthly has by far the highest conversion rate (35.9%)** but the lowest click volume (323). These are users who want the cheapest entry point and convert fast (~2.4 hours). The low click volume suggests not many personas are being routed to this plan, or it's not prominently featured.

**Monthly plans convert at 2-5x the rate of their yearly equivalents.** Pro Monthly converts at 12.9% vs. Pro Yearly at 7.3%. Pro+ Monthly at 14.8% vs. Pro+ Yearly at 10.8%. Users are more willing to commit to a lower upfront cost, and they do it faster (2-3 hours vs. 10-12 hours for annual plans).

**Pro Yearly is the highest-volume plan click (5,464) but converts at only 7.3%.** This is likely the "default" or most-promoted plan, attracting a lot of window-shoppers. It's also worth noting that 5,464 people clicked Pro Yearly but the entire pricing page only produced 429 total subscriptions — so the vast majority of Pro Yearly clickers go somewhere else.

**88% of plan-clickers click 2+ different plans** — nearly everyone is comparison-shopping across plans before deciding. This is healthy behavior but also suggests the plan differentiation or value proposition at the plan screen may need work to help users commit.

